Important notes:
-----------------

1. Strings are character array ending with '\0'. '\0' is 
   called String Terminator.

2. ways to output strings :

	char name[] = "Sanjay";
	printf("%s\n", name);
	puts(name);

3. ways to input strings:

	char name[30];
	scanf("%s",name);
	gets(name);

4. Useful string functions :

	int1 = strlen(str); /* returns length of string str */
	strcpy(target, source); /* copies source string to target string */
	strcat(target, source); /* appends source at the end of target */
	int1 = strcmp(str1, str2); /* returns 0 if strings are equal, 
                		      nonzero if they are unequal */
	strupr(str); /* converts string str to uppercase */
	strlwr(str); /* converts string str to lowercase */
	toupper(ch); /* convers character ch to uppercase */
	tolower(ch); /* converts character ch to lowercase */

5. #include<string.h> for prototypes of library string functions. 
